The paper discusses the use of deep autoencoders for efficient reinforcement learning on embedded systems. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories. The use of image data and convolutional neural networks suggests cs.CV as a likely category as well. The discussion of autonomous policies and embedded systems suggests cs.RO and cs.SY as possible categories.
